# help/en/overview.ftl — Nordic Dark Theme help texts (English)

help-nordic-dark-title = Nordic Dark Theme

help-nordic-dark-body =
    Nordic Dark is inspired by the popular Nord color palette — a calm, focused
    dark theme with muted arctic tones. Unlike Midnight Blue's vivid cyan, Nordic
    Dark uses softer arctic blues and cool grays that are easier on the eyes for
    extended use in moderate lighting.

    Color palette:
    - Background: dark polar night grays (#2e3440, #3b4252, #434c5e) — the Nord
      Polar Night colors
    - Accent: arctic blue (#88c0d0) from the Nord Frost palette
    - Text: soft snow white (#eceff4, #d8dee9) — Nord Snow Storm
    - Status: Nord Aurora colors — green, amber, red in muted variants

    The theme has lower contrast than Midnight Blue, which some users prefer for
    daytime or moderate-light environments.

help-nordic-dark-apply-title = Applying the Theme

help-nordic-dark-apply-body =
    1. Open Desktop Settings > Appearance > Theme.
    2. Select "Nordic Dark" from the theme list.
    3. Click Apply. Changes take effect immediately — no logout required.

    Note: Nordic Dark uses the Nord palette. If you use applications with their
    own Nord theme support (e.g. terminal emulators), they will align visually
    with FreeSynergy's Nordic Dark theme.
